I.    Introduction

A Risk Management Program has been implemented at the Nutrien Ag Solutions facility located at 1801 Broadway Street in Marseilles, Illinois, for the reduction of accidental releases of hazardous materials. This updated, five (5) year Risk Management Plan (RMP) summarizes the management, administrative, procedural, and technological controls that work together to minimize the risk to site personnel, contractors, visitors, and the community and environment at large of hazardous chemical releases. The RMP is organized to correspond with specific U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) RMP, Program 3 of 40 CFR 68, definitions and requirements of Subpart G, including: 

?    Introduction;

?    Nutrien Ag Solutions policies to protect health, environment, and safety;

?    Facility identification and regulated substances covered processes;

?    Hazard Assessment;

?    Prevention Program;

?    Five-Year Accident History;

?    Emergency Response Plan; 

?    Emergency Communications;

?    Spill Reporting / Environmental Release Procedures;

?    Planned changes to improve safety; and

?    Management Program



II.    Nutrien Ag Solutions Policies To Protect Health, Environment, and Safety

Risk management and safety are important concerns at Nutrien Ag Solutions; this RMP formalizes and documents these activities. Nutrien Ag Solutions is committed to conducting its operations in a safe and responsible manner and to reducing risks to human health and to the environment. It is Nutrien Ag Solutions's policy to comply with all applicable federal, state, and local rules and regulations.  This updated risk management plan is being submitted to comply with EPA 40 CFR 68 requirements to submit a risk management plan, every five (5) years.



